By default `distinctUntilChanged` uses `===` (`Object.is` in v7), which rejects emissions only when the reference matches. A custom comparer `(a, b) => boolean` lets you redefine equality — e.g. compare deep fields, normalise case, or hash a subset of properties. The operator still tracks only the previous value, so memory stays O(1).

