`bufferTime` emits an array per window (`T[]`). `windowTime` emits a nested `Observable<T>` per window, letting you apply further operators (e.g. `scan`, `reduce`, `toArray`) before flattening. Windows are ideal when you need per-window pipelines, not just flat batches.

